<p itemprop="description">A senior test manager provides strategic leadership for testing and quality assurance across multiple programmes and complex initiatives. They establish organisational testing capabilities, drive quality excellence, and manage senior testing teams to ensure digital services meet the highest standards.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide strategic leadership for testing and quality assurance across programmes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish organisational testing capabilities and quality frameworks</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead and manage senior testing teams across multiple complex projects</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive quality excellence and continuous improvement initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Partner with senior leadership on quality strategy and risk management</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish testing standards and governance processes</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Manage testing portfolios, budgets, and organisational resources</li>
    </ul>
</section>

